column19:
Everyone needs a place to lay their weary head. For travelers visiting Poipet, Poipet Resort Casino is an excellent choice for rest and rejuvenation. Well-known for its budget friendly environment and proximity to great restaurants, Poipet Resort Casino makes it easy to enjoy the best of Poipet.
You’ll enjoy relaxing rooms that offer a minibar, air conditioning, and a refrigerator, and you can stay connected during your stay as Poipet Resort Casino offers guests free wifi.
The hotel features a 24 hour front desk, a concierge, and 24 hour check-in. Plus, Poipet Resort Casino offers a sauna and an on-site restaurant, providing a pleasant respite from your busy day. For guests with a vehicle, parking is available.
Travelers looking for a place to eat close to Poipet Resort Casino can head to Destiny Café (1.2 mi) or Palm Coffee (0.9 mi), all of which are within walking distance.

column19: Open Studio Cambodia is an artist collective based in Siem Reap comprised of seven contemporary Cambodian artists and its founder, paper cutaway artist, Lauren Iida (Seattle, USA). Open Studio Cambodia provides mentorship, marketing, art supplies, and domestic and international exhibition opportunities to its members and collaborates with a network of artists and arts organizations to promote the rising contemporary art scene in Cambodia as a whole. We also offer events, contemporary art tours, and art-making workshops at our Siem Reap, Cambodia studio and around the country. Our physical location is temporarily closed due to the pandemic. Please visit our EXHIBITIONS page to see our work or shop online. Free domestic shipping and affordable international shipping available.

column19:
Ly Monaco Hotel is an excellent choice for travelers visiting Sisophon, offering many helpful amenities designed to enhance your stay.
You’ll enjoy relaxing rooms that offer a minibar and air conditioning, and you can stay connected during your stay as Ly Monaco Hotel offers guests free wifi.
The small hotel features a 24 hour front desk. Plus, Ly Monaco Hotel offers an on-site restaurant, providing a pleasant respite from your busy day. For guests with a vehicle, free parking is available.
When you’re feeling hungry, be sure to check out Kim Heng, which is an Asian restaurant that is popular with locals and out-of-towners alike.
Enjoy your stay in Sisophon!

Ly Heng Chhay Hotel puts the best of Poipet at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.

column19:
If you’re looking for a family-friendly hotel in Siem Reap, look no further than Angkor Riviera Hotel.
For those interested in checking out popular landmarks while visiting Siem Reap, Angkor Riviera Hotel is located a short distance from Wat Preah Prom Rath (0.2 mi) and Viti's Tuk Tuk Driver (0.6 mi).
Guest rooms offer air conditioning, and Angkor Riviera Hotel makes getting online easy as free wifi is available.
You can also take advantage of some of the amenities offered by the hotel, including a concierge and room service. In addition, guests can enjoy a pool and free breakfast during their visit. As an added convenience, there is free parking available to guests.
Siem Reap has plenty of barbeque restaurants. So when you’re here, be sure to check out popular spots like Khmer Grill Restaurant, Rina's Khmer Kitchen, and The Monsoon Asian Fusion and Bistro, which are serving up some great dishes.
Looking to explore? Then look no further than Pub Street (0.3 mi), which is a popular Siem Reap attraction – and it is conveniently located within walking distance of the hotel.
The staff at Angkor Riviera Hotel looks forward to serving you during your upcoming visit.

column19:
The villa is located about 5 minutes drives by bike from the city center (old market and pub street) and about 20 minutes drives by bike from famous buddhist temple - Angkor Wat. It is very safe and guiet place.

Villa is located near with Angkor Panorama Museum, Grace Village Church, Two Pursat Pagodas and famous Angkor Wat.

We recommend downloading and installing the PassApp Cambodia application. This is a cheap tuk tuk and car taxi service. 
Tuk Tuk for 4 pax is $18 around Angkor and extra charges $10 for Banteay Srei. 
Tuk Tuk to Old Market or Pub Street is $4 one way.

column19:
Finding an ideal budget friendly hotel in Battambang does not have to be difficult. Welcome to Spring Park Hotel, a nice option for travelers like you.
Given the close proximity of popular landmarks, such as Ta Dumbong Statue (0.4 mi) and White Elephant Pagoda (Wat Tahm-rai-saw) (0.6 mi), guests of Spring Park Hotel can easily experience some of Battambang's most well known attractions.
Rooms at Spring Park Hotel provide a refrigerator and a desk, and guests can stay connected with free wifi.
In addition, while staying at Spring Park Hotel guests have access to a 24 hour front desk, room service, and baggage storage. You can also enjoy a sauna and an on-site restaurant. Need a place to park? Parking is available at Spring Park Hotel.
Travelers looking to enjoy some dumplings  can head to Jaan Bai Restaurant, The Lonely Tree Cafe, or lan Chov Khorko Miteanh Chinese Noodle Restaurant. Otherwise, you may want to check out a cafe such as Choco L'Art Café, Hoc Cafe, or The Lonely Tree Cafe.
During your visit, be sure to check out HUMAN Gallery - Joseba Etxebarria Photography (0.5 mi), which is a popular attraction within walking distance of the hotel.
Spring Park Hotel looks forward to welcoming you on your visit to Battambang.

column19: Bat Cave Home Stay is a simple, affordable, and very cozy accommodation located 13 km from Battambang town and surrounded by acres of tropical greenery. Here we will provide you with shared bathrooms with hot and cold water, as well as Khmer bath towels. From your private balcony and from all the rooms, you can enjoy a beautiful view of a rice field. A fan and mosquito net are included as well. The Bat Cave in Phnom Sampue is 500 meters from our homestay. The famous Bamboo Train and Banana Temple are approximately 9 km from us, and Psar Nar is 13 km. You can use the bicycles for free. We offer complimentary pickup services from the bus and boat stations.

column19:
Au Cabaret Vert is known as the Romantic OASIS in Battambang !!! Dedicated to French Poet RIMBAUD, Au Cabaret Vert is a Eco resort hotel with first natural pool in the heart of Battambang. In a charming tropical garden, our villas (each villa is named with a poem of RIMBAUD) with private terrace offer a moment of serenity before discovering the charm of Battambang: authentic handicrafts, gorgeous landscape and exotic countryside.Our team will recommend you the best tours of Battambang.After your day trip, let's order a cocktail at the poolside to watch the sunset, and then enjoy our French and Cambodian fine cuisine.Free Wifi -Private Terrace - Room Service.
Come to Enjoy the French Style : UNIQUE in Battambang !

column19: Ganesha is situated in the Hart of Battambang Town on the quiet traditional street 1.5! Close to the main Market. Attachted with restaurant and bar with pool table kicker table and boardgames. We have created a different special atmosphere for our Guest that you will not find very often in Cambodia! Our Rooms and Dorms are comfortable clean and well ventilated! Dorms are only for 5 people, 4 clean Bathroom for 10 people! Room's private bathroom! Cold at night! Sitting area on both floors! Ganesha is about meeting people and to exchange experience! Our goals are making Ganesha Guest more aware of the way they are travelling and to learn more about Cambodia. We are not running this guesthouse only to get positive reviews! If you like to learn more about Cambodia, have a new experience speak with people and get lost sometime in a beautiful countryside. Have a great anventure!!

column19:
See why so many travelers make VY CHHE Hotel their hotel of choice when visiting Battambang. Providing an ideal mix of value, comfort and convenience, it offers a budget friendly setting with an array of amenities designed for travelers like you.
While staying at VY CHHE Hotel, visitors can check out White Elephant Pagoda (Wat Tahm-rai-saw) (0.2 mi) and Prasat Sneung (0.6 mi), some of Battambang's top attractions.
As your “home away from home,” the hotel rooms offer a flat screen TV, air conditioning, and a minibar, and getting online is easy, with free wifi available.
Guests have access to a 24 hour front desk, a concierge, and 24 hour check-in while staying at VY CHHE Hotel. In addition, VY CHHE Hotel offers free instant coffee, which will help make your Battambang trip additionally gratifying. And, as an added convenience, there is free parking available to guests.

column19: Located in Battambang's historic city centre, King Fy Hotel offers modern rooms with the latest conveniences - air-con, free Wi-Fi, 32" Flat Screen TV with satellite channels. Free pick up from the dock, bus stations, and shuttles to the shopping areas. Rooms appointed to the highest standards with private balcony & views of the Sangke River. A safe, minibar, and writing desk are included. Bathrooms have a rain shower or spa bathtub. The hotel is on the Sangke river in the historic centre near Wat Kandal and Wat Pacha and the Museum. Guests can rent a bicycle, or have us arrange a tour to the surrounding pagodas and temples in the spectacular countryside. The hotel has spa treatments, a mini-mart & souvenir shop, laundry services, a conference centre - currency can be exchanged. Our Coriander Restaurant specialises in Asian and European cuisine. Beautiful sunset views and cocktails can be enjoyed at our Terrestrial Lounge.

Everyone needs a place to lay their weary head. For travelers visiting Battambang, Khemara Battambang Hotel is an excellent choice for rest and rejuvenation. Well-known for its family-friendly environment and proximity to great restaurants and attractions, Khemara Battambang Hotel makes it easy to enjoy the best of Battambang.
You’ll enjoy relaxing rooms that offer air conditioning and a refrigerator, and you can stay connected during your stay as Khemara Battambang Hotel offers guests free wifi.
Plus, Khemara Battambang Hotel offers a pool and an on-site restaurant, providing a pleasant respite from your busy day. For guests with a vehicle, free parking is available.
While staying at Khemara Battambang Hotel, visitors can check out White Elephant Pagoda (Wat Tahm-rai-saw) (0.4 mi) and Ta Dumbong Statue (0.6 mi), some of Battambang's top attractions.
While visiting Battambang, you may want to try some dumplings  at one of the nearby restaurants, such as Jaan Bai Restaurant, The Lonely Tree Cafe, or lan Chov Khorko Miteanh Chinese Noodle Restaurant.
If you’re looking for something to do, HUMAN Gallery - Joseba Etxebarria Photography (0.4 mi) is a nice way to spend some time, and it is within walking distance of Khemara Battambang Hotel.
Whether you’re traveling for business, pleasure or both, Khemara Battambang Hotel is sure to make your visit to Battambang one worth remembering.

column19:
See why so many travelers make Banan Hotel their inn of choice when visiting Battambang. Providing an ideal mix of value, comfort and convenience, it offers a budget friendly setting with an array of amenities designed for travelers like you.
Nearby landmarks such as Ta Dumbong Statue (0.1 mi) and White Elephant Pagoda (Wat Tahm-rai-saw) (1.0 mi) make Banan Hotel a great place to stay when visiting Battambang.
Guest rooms offer a minibar, air conditioning, and a refrigerator, and Banan Hotel makes getting online easy as free wifi is available.
You can also take advantage of some of the amenities offered by the inn, including a concierge and room service. As an added convenience, there is free parking available to guests.
If you’re looking for a barbeque restaurant, consider a visit to Battambang BBQ & Buffet, which is not far from Banan Hotel.
Plus, during your trip, don’t forget to check out some of the popular ancient ruins, such as Prasat Sneung and Ek Phnom.
At Banan Hotel, your comfort and satisfaction come first, and they look forward to welcoming you to Battambang.

column19: Phka Villa Hotel is owned and run by a local family. With its location in the heart of the city, guests readily savor easy access to various attractions. It is only a 10 minutes’ walk to Battambang Museum and Psar Nat shopping center, an hour from Sisophon City, and two hours from Piopet Border. Phka Villa Hotel is a fine retreat, offering a large outdoor swimming pool decked beautifully with cozy sun-loungers. Rooms are furnished in the Khmer tradition, unleashing a pure thrill of the local lifestyle. All guestrooms are set around the pool and equipped with two private verandas and a bathroom, as well as modern facilities including cable TV and Wi-Fi. The restaurant serves authentically local flavors, and the bar serves the self-acclaimed best cocktails in town. Other services include massage treatments, laundry, tours and ticketing, a city and airport shuttle, and around-the-clock front desk assistance.

column19:
Looking for a place to stay in Battambang? Then look no further than Happy Villa Battambang, a hotel that brings the best of Battambang to your doorstep.
You’ll enjoy relaxing rooms that offer a minibar, a kitchenette, and a seating area, bringing comfort and convenience to your visit.
The hotel features room service. Plus, Happy Villa Battambang offers an on-site restaurant, providing a pleasant respite from your busy day. For guests with a vehicle, free parking is available.
For those interested in checking out popular landmarks while visiting Battambang, Happy Villa Battambang is located a short distance from White Elephant Pagoda (Wat Tahm-rai-saw) (1.6 mi) and Battambang Crocodile Farm (2.3 mi).
Travelers looking to enjoy some bibimbap  can head to Cafe Eden. Otherwise, you may want to check out an Asian restaurant such as Jaan Bai Restaurant, Smokin' Pot, or Nary Kitchen.
There is no shortage of things to do in the area: explore popular ancient ruins such as Prasat Sneung and Ek Phnom.
We’re sure you’ll enjoy your stay at Happy Villa Battambang as you experience everything Battambang has to offer.

column19: Grill Wine Café is the bright new concept of dinning venue, which envisions being the one-stop dining venue to serve your every need. The well-selected breakfast menu ranges from Western to Asian, from traditional to contemporary Khmer cuisine. Its great location makes GWC become the special meeting point that suitable for either your relaxed lunch schedule or quick bite of snacks with refreshing smoothies, frappe, coffee or tea providing an unparalleled dining experience. At Grill Wine Café, dinner is not a simple meal but to feast and celebrate the great dining experience, you cannot miss the grill of world class sausages by International Master Butcher who joined recipes of our head Chef which newly creates the great infusion of Cambodian Amok sausage, curry sausage...and a stunning wine cellar consists of more than one hundred of wines from all over the world.

column19: Miss Wong Cocktail Bar has been a mainstay in the Cambodian bar scene for a decade and has now opened a second establishment in the Sino-French heritage quarter of Battambang. For the past ten years Miss Wong has gained a reputation, not just in Cambodia but also internationally, as a sophisticated cocktail bar serving premium spirits, providing professional service with an elegantly designed décor. Unlike the 1930’s old Shanghai speakeasy themed Siem Reap establishment, Miss Wong Battambang is embracing a more Chinoiserie style. Open from 4pm to Midnight daily and serving innovative cocktails and handcrafted Dim Sum.

column19: ROMCHEIK 5 is nominated in the TOP 10 BEST INDEPENDENT Art spaces in S.E. Asia and N° 1 in Cambodia (The Guardian / November 2017) ! Romcheik 5 is the name of the neighbourhood of Battambang where, in 2012, 4 young artists have established their studios with the help of a donor. In 2015, this space has been extended with the construction of a building sheltering an art gallery and since October 2018 a real Museum with a permanent collection of their best artworks. On rooftop you will find a nice Café with a large scale of foods and drinks .The entrance to the all site is charged 5$ (discount 2 $ 50), to contribute to the maintenance of the premises and the purchase of artist materials.

column19: How about local living experience with my family in Battambang. We’re offering accommodations, foods and drinks, I am sure you will love it. We’re a local family live in Battambang since Pol Pot error ends. My dad, who survived after the war in 1975 till 1979 can share his experiences during that war. He is one of the luckiest who survived during this awful time, now you can have chance to talk to him and he will reveal what was happening than. Our accommodations is very basic, we lives at wooden house, there is a kitchen, three bathrooms, good shower , a place where you can hang out for a coffee, tea and snacks, we would like to offer you cooking our traditional foods too, We have a lovely neighborhood, there are coffee stand, secondary school, old temple, clinics near by. Some farms around it, especially close to the city about 10 minutes by walk to the city.

column19: Jaan Bai is a home for folks who share our love of gatherings around the table, our passion for food and our interest in supporting Cambodian youth. We are focused on the training and professional development of Cambodian youth, with all profits going towards the overall sustainability of CCT. Our cuisine is all about the simplicity of well crafted, nourishing and wholesome recipes. We use seasonal organic produce sourced from our kitchen garden, local farmers and neighbouring markets. column19: We welcome everyone! Our vision (what we hope to be and achieve)We wish to help Cambodian students to become opinion leaders in future with profits that we make. Currently we have several students working with us as our scholars. They work and study hard to learn different cultures, languages and manners so that they can pass what they have learnt to the locals. We teach them how to work together as a team and how to serve.Our mission (What we are here for)We aim to touch and enhance the lives of people through our Christian culur of quality care and service. Also with our enthusiasm, team work and values, we offer the best possible drinks and food.Our values (What underlies our way of doing things)Respect, integrity, compassion, justice and innovation. Your patronage and ongoing support of the caféJireh is very much appreciated.Functions at caféJirehSpecial occasion coming up? Want to have it at a venue that will go that bit extra in customer service and presentation to ensure that your experience will be one to remember? At café jireh, with luxurious service, wonderful company and a relaxed atmosphere, it is a recipe for a memorable birthday parties, anniversary or special events. caféJireh caters for events if up to 20 people. Bookings necessary.

column19: Located in Battambang's historic city centre, King Fy Hotel offers modern rooms with the latest conveniences - air-con, free Wi-Fi, 32" Flat Screen TV with satellite channels. Free pick up from the dock, bus stations, and shuttles to the shopping areas. Rooms appointed to the highest standards with private balcony & views of the Sangke River. A safe, minibar, and writing desk are included. Bathrooms have a rain shower or spa bathtub. The hotel is on the Sangke river in the historic centre near Wat Kandal and Wat Pacha and the Museum. Guests can rent a bicycle, or have us arrange a tour to the surrounding pagodas and temples in the spectacular countryside. The hotel has spa treatments, a mini-mart & souvenir shop, laundry services, a conference centre - currency can be exchanged. Our Coriander Restaurant specialises in Asian and European cuisine. Beautiful sunset views and cocktails can be enjoyed at our Terrestrial Lounge.

column19: THE TWIZT LIFESTYLE HOSTEL & HOTEL Ideally centered in the heart of Siem Reap’s bustling walking street of 16th Avenue, The Twizt is characterized as a “flashpacking hostel” featuring astonishing and modern interior design, perfect for generation Z. At Twizt, life is all FUN! Stay in for great food and drinks to get the chance to socialize with like-minded peeps around Siem Reap’s largest AKAS Bar featuring the infinity swimming pool and a tropical beach located on the rooftop overlooking the horizon of the Cambodia’s historical city.

column19: Dear all Travellers You want to visit Battambang and Real Cambodia? My name is Savet a former of English teacher from 2010 to 2014 and graduated University in 2013 major of Human Resource Management. Now I work as a tour guide and Tuk Tuk driver base in Battambang. I would like to introduce my unique tour program if you have one day to visit Battambang. What makes us different? - We mix bike tour and Tuk Tuk tour in a day. - We do explore village life by bikes so this is the best way to know Real Cambodia. It is my own village where i was born so i will show you how we live and enjoy cycling around beautiful countryside. - We offer you a local lunch that will be prepared by my wife. - You will have a chance to meet friendly local people and they are so happy to meet you. - We are happy during the tour if you have more questions to ask.

column19: Our vision is to position MAISONS WAT KOR, BATTAMBANG as the premier destination where guests experience the harmonious blend of Cambodia's serene countryside, eco-conscious practices, and rich Khmer heritage. We aspire to be recognized as a beacon of sustainable tourism, offering a haven of tranquility and cultural immersion for discerning travelers seeking authentic experiences. Our goal is to foster local talent and expertise in the hospitality industry, empowering village communities to directly benefit from our presence. By providing training, employment opportunities, and support for local businesses, we aim to contribute to the sustainable development of the community while delivering exceptional experiences to our guests.

column18: Tep Kao Sol Loeum Lorn Gallery
column19: Welcome to TEP KAO SOL and LOEUM LORN GALLERY. We are an art gallery and a shop in the center of Battambang, which is the artistic and cultural city of Cambodia. On the first floor we exhibit and sell watercolors, drawings and reproductions of Cambodian painters and artists. On the second floor, you can discover the astonishing ice painting work of Loeum Lorn.

column19: Welcome to YOUR home away from home, welcome to OUR home! Sangker Villa is a Guest House with 8 rooms where you can feel absolutely at home! We would be delighted to help you organize your stay here and give you the best advice possible for you to enjoy discovering Battambang and its surroundings. You can relax in our salt water pool, have a drink at our bar and enjoy our lovely breakfast with fresh, home-made bread. Welcome home! Our Guest house offers 8 rooms in a "modern-khmer'' style. Five STANDARD rooms on the ground floor and three rooms upstairs, including one standard room, one DELUXE room and one DELUXE with BALCONY. In our villa you can enjoy the warm and friendly atmosphere at the bar overlooking the pool. We serve iced tea, homemade YAO sorbets made at Sangker Villa homemade lemonade, espresso coffee, draft beers, plenty of cocktails, French and Australian wines, We also serve snacks on request: tuna sandwiches, pasta salad, vegetarian tabbouleh, omelet ..

column19: In 2015 the humanitarian photographer Joseba Etxebarria settles in Battambang, Cambodia, aware of his degree of responsibility towards the "voiceless". Convinced that he has the necessary tools to create a space with the power to inspire change, in June 2017 he founded Human Gallery in the city of Battambang, a magical place where he shares his work, as well as the human stories that there is behind Human Gallery collects many of the photographs that Joseba took during his world tour for Human Rights (2010-2022). * 20% of the sale of the photographs exhibited in the gallery, or on the web, is used to cover the education of the children who are beneficiaries of our children's project "Wings for the future".

column19: ROMCHEIK 5 is nominated in the TOP 10 BEST INDEPENDENT Art spaces in S.E. Asia and N° 1 in Cambodia (The Guardian / November 2017) ! Romcheik 5 is the name of the neighbourhood of Battambang where, in 2012, 4 young artists have established their studios with the help of a donor. In 2015, this space has been extended with the construction of a building sheltering an art gallery and since October 2018 a real Museum with a permanent collection of their best artworks. On rooftop you will find a nice Café with a large scale of foods and drinks .The entrance to the all site is charged 5$ (discount 2 $ 50), to contribute to the maintenance of the premises and the purchase of artist materials.

column19: Lux Guesthouse is a modern luxury guest house which has high quality standard service with the unique Khmer hospitality you expect and deserve. It is only a 5 minute walk to the Central Market and by bike, it is less than 2 minutes. Of course, tuk tuks are always an option as well. Run by Khmer family, it is a friendly place with a warm, cozy atmosphere and it will provide you with a memorable experience of Khmer hospitality .

column19: Welcome to YOUR home away from home, welcome to OUR home! Sangker Villa is a Guest House with 8 rooms where you can feel absolutely at home! We would be delighted to help you organize your stay here and give you the best advice possible for you to enjoy discovering Battambang and its surroundings. You can relax in our salt water pool, have a drink at our bar and enjoy our lovely breakfast with fresh, home-made bread. Welcome home! Our Guest house offers 8 rooms in a "modern-khmer'' style. Five STANDARD rooms on the ground floor and three rooms upstairs, including one standard room, one DELUXE room and one DELUXE with BALCONY. In our villa you can enjoy the warm and friendly atmosphere at the bar overlooking the pool. We serve iced tea, homemade YAO sorbets made at Sangker Villa homemade lemonade, espresso coffee, draft beers, plenty of cocktails, French and Australian wines, We also serve snacks on request: tuna sandwiches, pasta salad, vegetarian tabbouleh, omelet ..

column19: Wat Banan temple away from Battambang city about 25km. It’s a 358-stone-step climb up Phnom Banan to reach Prasat Banan, but the incredible views across surrounding countryside from the top are worth it. Udayadityavarman II, son of Suryavarman I, built Prasat Banan in the 11th century; some locals claim the five-tower layout here was the inspiration for Angkor Wat, although this seems optimistic.

column18: Discover Battambang with Samol Tuk-Tuk & Motorbike Tours
column19: Hello! My name is Samol, I am 37years old and from Battambang, Cambodia. I have a degree in Management and Tourism and am currently a local guide! I speak English and a little French. To afford my studies and daily living expenses, I have decided to create a permanent tour operation. If you are looking to tour Battambang I offer tuk-tuk, motorbike and guide services. With over 10 years of experience guiding travelers I have a wealth of knowledge that I would love to share with you! Let me educate you on my home town and show you some of Battambang's best sites. But we are Human Animal and living in the same world and same planet and moreover, Battambang is so beautiful and has a lot of things to see. column5: {'label': 'The Battambang Bike, 021410 បាត់ដំបង, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'បាត់ដំបង', 'city': 'បាត់ដំបង', 'district': 'ស្វាយប៉ោ', 'postalCode': '021410'}
column19: The Battambang Bike offer tours of downtown Battambang's art and architecture, custom tours, bike rentals and repairs, and Saturday Fun Rides. Our signature CITY TOUR OF BATTAMBANG will leave you in love with this gorgeous city. Hop on one of our bikes and let our guide take you on an interactive tour of Battambang's historical downtown, with rich explanations of the area's history and dynamic contemporary arts' scene, Cambodian culture, and urban planning. We also have EVENING TOURS, departing daily at 4:00pm, which show off the wonders of Battambang’s activity and architecture as the sun is setting. We will take you to one of the tallest buildings in town for a bird’s eye view, a visit to a wat at sunset, and stops at locals’ favorite exercise spots and restaurants, which are especially popular around dusk.Or join us for a FREE SATURDAY FUN RIDE. Whether we are exploring Battambang’s religious buildings, heading out to the old airport to learn from the city’s only BMX teacher, or training for a longer road race, we always have fun and get great exercise.

column19: First Cycling Tour Agency offers bicycle and walking tours in the city of Battambang – founded by Raksa Soy and Rida Phin in 2017. Growing up in Battambang, both Raksa and Rida attended the University of Battambang. After graduating, both decided to start the First Cycling Tour to provide tourists with information on cultural, historical and contemporary heritage in their beloved city. Our aim is to help and share with all of the visitors our beautiful and interesting places in Battambang. Battambang is a beautiful city in Cambodia. There are many rich aspects of the Khmer culture. There are many beautiful places, architecture, colorful markets, nice view of temples, fishing villages, beautiful landscapes and fields of rural villages. First Cycling Tour is not just a tour company but a place where we help young students to gain experience by working in our shop. We welcome students who have a dream and passion to own their own business. Here, we share our knowledge and experience.

column19: Mr Tour Battambang is a tour company founded by Rysa in 2019. We provide bicycle tours around Battambang and you will be able to explore both the city and the countryside. Our mission is to help poor Cambodian children by breaking the cycle of poverty through education. We will fund their studies and help their families by using money from the tour. column19: Dear all Travellers You want to visit Battambang and Real Cambodia? My name is Savet a former of English teacher from 2010 to 2014 and graduated University in 2013 major of Human Resource Management. Now I work as a tour guide and Tuk Tuk driver base in Battambang. I would like to introduce my unique tour program if you have one day to visit Battambang. What makes us different? - We mix bike tour and Tuk Tuk tour in a day. - We do explore village life by bikes so this is the best way to know Real Cambodia. It is my own village where i was born so i will show you how we live and enjoy cycling around beautiful countryside. - We offer you a local lunch that will be prepared by my wife. - You will have a chance to meet friendly local people and they are so happy to meet you. - We are happy during the tour if you have more questions to ask.

column19: Dirtbike Expeditions offer a truly unparalleled and remarkable journey that can take you off the beaten track and into some of the most isolated and remarkable destinations. You will explore unknown terrain, experience breathtaking views, discover hidden gems, and uncover stories in places that have remained untouched by many. With our experienced guide, you can traverse rugged terrain, cross rivers and streams, scale steep cliffside paths, and experience cultures that are inaccessible to most travelers. There is no doubt that this type of expedition will provide you with an unforgettable experience that will be remembered for years to come.

column19: The Cambodia Peace Gallery, opened in October 2018, is a new space for learning, sharing and reflecting on Cambodia's journey from war towards peace. Exhibits are focused on how Cambodians worked together to end the war, the recovery process, and working towards reconciliation for the future. Emphasis is given to positive stories of strength, resilience, and overcoming adversities.

column5: {'label': 'Chhouk Restaurant, 021401 បាត់ដំបង, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'បាត់ដំបង', 'city': 'បាត់ដំបង', 'district': 'ទួលតាឯក', 'postalCode': '021401'}
column19:
Welcome to Phka Chhouk Tep Guesthouse, your Battambang “home away from home.” Phka Chhouk Tep Guesthouse aims to make your visit as relaxing and enjoyable as possible, which is why so many guests continue to come back year after year.
Close to some of Battambang's most popular landmarks, such as Ta Dumbong Statue (0.2 mi) and Prasat Sneung (0.5 mi), Phka Chhouk Tep Guesthouse is a great destination for tourists.
The rooms offer a flat screen TV, air conditioning, and a desk, and getting online is possible, as free wifi is available, allowing you to rest and refresh with ease.
Phka Chhouk Tep Guesthouse features a concierge, room service, and baggage storage. Guests arriving by vehicle have access to parking.
While you’re here, be sure to check out some of the Asian restaurants, including Jaan Bai Restaurant, Smokin' Pot, and Nary Kitchen, all of which are a short distance from Phka Chhouk Tep Guesthouse.
If you are interested in exploring Battambang, check out one of the art galleries, such as HUMAN Gallery - Joseba Etxebarria Photography, ROMCHEIK 5 Art Space, and La Fabrik.
Phka Chhouk Tep Guesthouse puts the best of Battambang at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.

column19:
Au Cabaret Vert is known as the Romantic OASIS in Battambang !!! Dedicated to French Poet RIMBAUD, Au Cabaret Vert is a Eco resort hotel with first natural pool in the heart of Battambang. In a charming tropical garden, our villas (each villa is named with a poem of RIMBAUD) with private terrace offer a moment of serenity before discovering the charm of Battambang: authentic handicrafts, gorgeous landscape and exotic countryside.Our team will recommend you the best tours of Battambang.After your day trip, let's order a cocktail at the poolside to watch the sunset, and then enjoy our French and Cambodian fine cuisine.Free Wifi -Private Terrace - Room Service.
Come to Enjoy the French Style : UNIQUE in Battambang !

column19: The Lonely Tree Café is a social enterprise with the goal to obtain profits to help finance the social projects of the Apostolic Prefecture of Battambang. The projects we support cover a wide range of humanitarian aid including education, support for the disabled, healthcare and preservation of Cambodian cultural heritage. At the Lonely Tree Café we give employment to underprivileged and disabled people: the staff consist of vulnerable youth and most of the products sold in the Lonely Tree Store are crafted by people with physical disabilities who are in permanent need.

column19: Bar Ang is an open & airy oasis in the city located on the 2nd floor of our home. The restaurant & small bar make one feel like family immediately. We are not fancy nore think of ourselves as "5 star" we simply enjoy what we do and it shows. We serve classic Khmei dishes using organic ingredients from our garden and when possible from friends who farm. Our small menu of curry, amok and burgers offer large satisfying portions. Our cocktails use fresh seasonal fruits. We play eclectic music and encourage solo travelers to chat. We pride ourselves on service and attention to detail as we are hands on management. Battambang Scooter & Motorcycle Rentals, in business for over 15 years, can also be found at BAR ANG. We offer rentals of both automatic and semi automatic units. We provide you with ideas on how to enjoy your time on one of our units.

column19: Soksabike is a social enterprise focusing on community development, vocational training school, and environmental protection in Battambang, Cambodia. As the first bicycle tour operator in Battambang, we have been offering people from all around the world an insight into the traditional livelihoods of the Cambodian countryside for over seven years. We place an emphasis on educating guests in the realities of life in rural Cambodia, and ensure that your visit makes a positive impact on the local communities. Plus your tour fee goes towards supporting the local families you visit on the tour and for vocational training for local university students. We believe touring Cambodia by bicycle provides a richer, personal and more interactive experience for visitors. Be sure to check out what happens on a Soksabike tour!

column19: ROMCHEIK 5 is nominated in the TOP 10 BEST INDEPENDENT Art spaces in S.E. Asia and N° 1 in Cambodia (The Guardian / November 2017) ! Romcheik 5 is the name of the neighbourhood of Battambang where, in 2012, 4 young artists have established their studios with the help of a donor. In 2015, this space has been extended with the construction of a building sheltering an art gallery and since October 2018 a real Museum with a permanent collection of their best artworks. On rooftop you will find a nice Café with a large scale of foods and drinks .The entrance to the all site is charged 5$ (discount 2 $ 50), to contribute to the maintenance of the premises and the purchase of artist materials.

column19: Jaan Bai is a home for folks who share our love of gatherings around the table, our passion for food and our interest in supporting Cambodian youth. We are focused on the training and professional development of Cambodian youth, with all profits going towards the overall sustainability of CCT. Our cuisine is all about the simplicity of well crafted, nourishing and wholesome recipes. We use seasonal organic produce sourced from our kitchen garden, local farmers and neighbouring markets. column19: The Lonely Tree Café is a social enterprise with the goal to obtain profits to help finance the social projects of the Apostolic Prefecture of Battambang. The projects we support cover a wide range of humanitarian aid including education, support for the disabled, healthcare and preservation of Cambodian cultural heritage. At the Lonely Tree Café we give employment to underprivileged and disabled people: the staff consist of vulnerable youth and most of the products sold in the Lonely Tree Store are crafted by people with physical disabilities who are in permanent need.

column19: ROMCHEIK 5 is nominated in the TOP 10 BEST INDEPENDENT Art spaces in S.E. Asia and N° 1 in Cambodia (The Guardian / November 2017) ! Romcheik 5 is the name of the neighbourhood of Battambang where, in 2012, 4 young artists have established their studios with the help of a donor. In 2015, this space has been extended with the construction of a building sheltering an art gallery and since October 2018 a real Museum with a permanent collection of their best artworks. On rooftop you will find a nice Café with a large scale of foods and drinks .The entrance to the all site is charged 5$ (discount 2 $ 50), to contribute to the maintenance of the premises and the purchase of artist materials.

column5: {'label': 'Princess KTV and Apsara Restaurant, 021410 បាត់ដំបង, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'បាត់ដំបង', 'city': 'បាត់ដំបង', 'district': 'ស្វាយប៉ោ', 'postalCode': '021410'}
column19: Bar Ang is an open & airy oasis in the city located on the 2nd floor of our home. The restaurant & small bar make one feel like family immediately. We are not fancy nore think of ourselves as "5 star" we simply enjoy what we do and it shows. We serve classic Khmei dishes using organic ingredients from our garden and when possible from friends who farm. Our small menu of curry, amok and burgers offer large satisfying portions. Our cocktails use fresh seasonal fruits. We play eclectic music and encourage solo travelers to chat. We pride ourselves on service and attention to detail as we are hands on management. Battambang Scooter & Motorcycle Rentals, in business for over 15 years, can also be found at BAR ANG. We offer rentals of both automatic and semi automatic units. We provide you with ideas on how to enjoy your time on one of our units.

column19: La Villa was constructed in the 1930's by a tradesman from Battambang, this colonial architecture was very fashionable during the French colonial period. The proprietor, Mr Eap Heo later bequeathed his home to his two youngest children who then lived in the residence till the coup d'etat in 1975. After the Khmer rouge period, the house became the general quarters for the Vietnamese army. It was given to a Cambodian general after their departure. For many years, the house was partially leased and squatted before it was sold in 2004 to a young expatriate couple who were mesmerized by the charm and beauty of this ancient house. After significant renovations, the house and its outbuildings regained its splendor in the form of a charming 7 bedroom guest house with a swimming pool that will captivate anyone that would like to re-live and experience an Indochinese atmosphere. column19:
If you’re looking for a budget friendly guest house in Siem Reap, look no further than Smiley's Guesthouse.
Close to some of Siem Reap's most popular landmarks, such as Wat Preah Prom Rath (0.5 mi) and Viti's Tuk Tuk Driver (0.6 mi), Smiley's Guesthouse is a great destination for tourists.
Guest rooms offer amenities such as air conditioning, and guests can go online with free wifi offered by the guest house.
Smiley`s Guesthouse Hotel features a 24 hour front desk, room service, and baggage storage, to help make your stay more enjoyable. The property also boasts a pool and an on-site restaurant.
While in Siem Reap be sure to experience local dumplings  favorites at Marum, Khmer Kitchen Restaurant, or Spoons.
There is no shortage of things to do in the area: explore popular art galleries such as Angkor Artwork E&T Stocker, Theam's House, and Jayav Art.
The staff at Smiley's Guesthouse looks forward to serving you during your upcoming visit.

column19:
Welcome to Bamboo train (Ou Dambong Village)!

Bamboo train mean norry or nori ( French word for lorry) is an improvised rail vehicle from Cambodia. Lonely Planet describes it as “Cambodia’s bamboo train”. Originally conceived as a logistical fix during the United Nations Transitional Authority of Cambodia period, the original “bamboo train” was a lorry system that operated on Cambodia’s rarely used northern rail line.

column19: Jaan Bai is a home for folks who share our love of gatherings around the table, our passion for food and our interest in supporting Cambodian youth. We are focused on the training and professional development of Cambodian youth, with all profits going towards the overall sustainability of CCT. Our cuisine is all about the simplicity of well crafted, nourishing and wholesome recipes. We use seasonal organic produce sourced from our kitchen garden, local farmers and neighbouring markets. This project has been made possible by Vittoria Coffee, Australia. Open 11:00 - 10:00 (kitchen closes at 9:00) Tuesday - Sunday.

column19: ROMCHEIK 5 is nominated in the TOP 10 BEST INDEPENDENT Art spaces in S.E. Asia and N° 1 in Cambodia (The Guardian / November 2017) ! Romcheik 5 is the name of the neighbourhood of Battambang where, in 2012, 4 young artists have established their studios with the help of a donor. In 2015, this space has been extended with the construction of a building sheltering an art gallery and since October 2018 a real Museum with a permanent collection of their best artworks. On rooftop you will find a nice Café with a large scale of foods and drinks .The entrance to the all site is charged 5$ (discount 2 $ 50), to contribute to the maintenance of the premises and the purchase of artist materials.

column19: Located on the rooftop of Romcheik 5 Artspace, it is the ideal place to eat & drink while recovering from your emotions after visiting the museum and art galleries . Open from 10 to 17 h for brunch , lunch or afternoon tea, we promise the nice view with fresh air. We believe that the combination of authentic art, beautiful space and high quality food & beverage could create an authentic experience. With the act of environment care, we use bamboo straw and reusable glass instead of the plastic.

column5: {'label': 'First Snow, 021410 បាត់ដំបង, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'បាត់ដំបង', 'city': 'បាត់ដំបង', 'district': 'ស្វាយប៉ោ', 'postalCode': '021410'}
column19: First Cycling Tour Agency offers bicycle and walking tours in the city of Battambang – founded by Raksa Soy and Rida Phin in 2017. Growing up in Battambang, both Raksa and Rida attended the University of Battambang. After graduating, both decided to start the First Cycling Tour to provide tourists with information on cultural, historical and contemporary heritage in their beloved city. Our aim is to help and share with all of the visitors our beautiful and interesting places in Battambang. Battambang is a beautiful city in Cambodia. There are many rich aspects of the Khmer culture. There are many beautiful places, architecture, colorful markets, nice view of temples, fishing villages, beautiful landscapes and fields of rural villages. First Cycling Tour is not just a tour company but a place where we help young students to gain experience by working in our shop. We welcome students who have a dream and passion to own their own business. Here, we share our knowledge and experience.

column19: Our vision is to position MAISONS WAT KOR, BATTAMBANG as the premier destination where guests experience the harmonious blend of Cambodia's serene countryside, eco-conscious practices, and rich Khmer heritage. We aspire to be recognized as a beacon of sustainable tourism, offering a haven of tranquility and cultural immersion for discerning travelers seeking authentic experiences. Our goal is to foster local talent and expertise in the hospitality industry, empowering village communities to directly benefit from our presence. By providing training, employment opportunities, and support for local businesses, we aim to contribute to the sustainable development of the community while delivering exceptional experiences to our guests.

column19: Phare Ponleu Selpak – "the Brightness of the Arts" in Khmer – is a non-profit arts school located in Battambang, Cambodia offering support to children, youth, and the surrounding communities through artistic, educational, and social support programs. ||| Circus shows happen every Monday, Thursday, and Saturday starting at 7 p.m. and doors open at 6 p.m. Arrive early to grab a cold drink, visit our art exhibition hall and shop in the boutique! ||| Free campus tours happen Monday-Friday at 8:30 a.m., 9:30 a.m., 10:30 a.m., and 2:30 p.m., 3:30 p.m. 4:30 p.m. Tours don't require a reservation.

column19: Royal Angkor Resort and Spa is conveniently perched along the gateway of some of the most significant archeological sites in SE-Asia, creating the ideal location to explore Cambodia's rich cultural inheritance. Tucked away from the hustle and noise of the city, Royal Angkor Resort is only minutes away from these iconic landmarks, providing unprecedented access to the legendary Angkor Wat, Angkor Thom and Bayon temples as well as the charming and historic town of Siem Reap. Stretching over two and a half hectares, this iconic Siem Reap hotel is jeweled with a beautiful tropical landscape and decorated with the most remarkable architecture, reminiscent of the early 20th century. From fine dining to traditional rooms and suites, Royal Angkor Resort & Spa combines ancient charm with modern-day leisure, creating the ultimate space to unwind and embrace the magical spirit of Cambodia.

column19: Located in the heart of Battambang, about a 3-minute drive by Tuk Tuk from the city center, Moloppor Villa offers courtyard-style accommodations with a shared kitchen and a garden with outdoor seating area. Free WiFi access is available at the property. Featuring traditional Khmer architecture, rooms and suite at Family's Guest House are equipped with a flat-screen TV, a DVD player and a mini-bar. The private bathrooms have a separate bathtub and walk-in shower. Guests can enjoy meals at the restaurant by the swimming pool. ATM and coffee shops can be found nearby. The property offers complimentary pick-up services from the bus or train stations. Siem Reap-Angkor International Airport is 99 mi from the property. This property is also rated for the best value in Battambang! Guests are getting more for their money when compared to other properties in this city. We speak your language!

column19: Ta Dumbong Kro Aung Statue ( Black man Statue ) Founded in the 11th century by the Khmer Empire, Battambang is the leading rice-producing province of the country. For nearly 100 years it was a major commercial hub and provincial capital of Siamese province of Inner Cambodia (1795-1907), though it was always populated by Khmer, with some ethnic Vietnamese, Lao, Thai and Chinese. Battambang remains the hub of Cambodia’s northwest, connecting the region with Phnom Penh and Thailand.

column19: Hanchey Bamboo Resort is a unique hidden gem, nestled in the quiet countryside 20 km from the city of Kampong Cham and overlooking the Mekong River. The resort offers a unique opportunity to practice Yoga and Meditation while enjoying the peace and tranquility of the Cambodian countryside. We cooperate with local NGO, Buddhism for Social Development Action (BSDA), providing training and work experience opportunities for disadvantage youth from the region through our Hospitality Training Centre. Our rates include a la carte-breakfast, dinner with three choices, use of swimming pool, complementary bikes as well as yoga and meditation classes. For our day visitors, Bamboo Restaurant offers delicious and locally sourced Khmer and Western dishes as well as refreshing drinks. We are looking forward to hosting you at our resort in the future.

column19:
Finding an ideal guest house in Kampong Cham does not have to be difficult. Welcome to Jolie Guesthouse, a nice option for travelers like you.
While staying at Jolie Guesthouse, visitors can check out Wat Nokor (1.6 mi), which is a popular Kampong Cham attraction.
Rooms at Jolie Guesthouse provide air conditioning and a minibar.
If you’re looking for a French restaurant, consider a visit to Destiny Coffee House, which is not far from Jolie Guesthouse.
If you’re looking for something to do, Ko Paen Bamboo Bridge (0.9 mi) and The French Tower (1.1 mi) are a nice way to spend some time, and they are all within walking distance of Jolie Guesthouse.
Jolie Guesthouse looks forward to welcoming you on your visit to Kampong Cham.

column5: {'label': 'Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub, 030402 កំពង់ចាម, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពង់ចាម', 'city': 'កំពង់ចាម', 'district': 'កំពង់ចាម', 'postalCode': '030402'}
column19:
Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub is an excellent choice for travelers visiting Kampong Cham, offering a budget friendly environment alongside many helpful amenities designed to enhance your stay.
Close to Wat Nokor (2.0 mi), a popular Kampong Cham landmark, Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub is a great destination for tourists.
Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub features a 24 hour front desk and baggage storage. In addition, as a valued Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub guest, you can enjoy an on-site restaurant that is available on-site. Guests arriving by vehicle have access to free parking.
While you’re here, be sure to check out LBN Asian Restaurant, one of the southwestern restaurants that can be found in Kampong Cham, which is a short distance from Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub.
Should time allow, Ko Paen Bamboo Bridge and The French Tower are some popular attractions that are within walking distance.
Enjoy your stay in Kampong Cham!

column19: In a luxurious garden with plenty of fruit trees, Mekong Bamboo Hut Guesthouse offers an amazing way to discover Cambodia.In the island of koh Pene in a middle of the Mekong river front of Kampong Cham, cross the biggest bamboo brige of Asia and come discover a Khmer traditional life style. In our Guesthouse, guests sleep in a hut, using a hammock or a matress with mosquito net for 3$/night. The place is very relaxing with a platform overlooking the Mekong. We have a bar restaurant with homemade food. Nice beach for swimming on the dry season.

column19: Please be advised Moha Oudom Hotel is under new management since March 2016. 24 hour security cameras have been installed and a security lockbox is located at reception. Moha Oudom is a Khmer style 40 room hotel located on the picturesque riverfront overlooking the Tonle Sap River (Mekong River). Enjoy spectacular river sunset views from our two large patio areas. Our rooms are varied and cater to all travellers. Choose from single, double or family rooms with either fan or airconditioning. All rooms feature windows, cable TV and en suite bathrooms with hot or cold showers. Wifi is available throughout the building. Here at Moha Oudom Hotel we can arrange local tours as well as bus tickets, bike rental and visa services. Khmer restaurants are located right next door and Western restaurants are just a 2 minute walk away. The local market (Psar Samaki) is just around the corner. ATMs are nearby. Walk or cycle along the shaded riverfront promenade.

column19:
Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub is an excellent choice for travelers visiting Kampong Cham, offering a budget friendly environment alongside many helpful amenities designed to enhance your stay.
Close to Wat Nokor (2.0 mi), a popular Kampong Cham landmark, Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub is a great destination for tourists.
Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub features a 24 hour front desk and baggage storage. In addition, as a valued Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub guest, you can enjoy an on-site restaurant that is available on-site. Guests arriving by vehicle have access to free parking.
While you’re here, be sure to check out LBN Asian Restaurant, one of the southwestern restaurants that can be found in Kampong Cham, which is a short distance from Mekong Crossing Guesthouse Restaurant & Pub.
Should time allow, Ko Paen Bamboo Bridge and The French Tower are some popular attractions that are within walking distance.
Enjoy your stay in Kampong Cham!

column19: LBN Asian Hotel is a well-established hospitality establishment known for its exemplary services and dedication to providing a comfortable stay for its guests. Located in a prime location in Kampong Cham, the hotel offers a range of amenities designed to cater to the needs of both business and leisure travellers. One of the notable features of LBN Asian Hotel is its location along of Mekong River, some rooms face to Mekong River and Kizuna Bridge and also each room is meticulously furnished and equipped with modern amenities such as comfortable bedding, Wi-Fi connectivity, and a well-appointed bathroom. The hotel also offers various room categories to suit the preferences and budgets of different guests. The hotel's dining options are also worth highlighting. LBN Asian Hotel boasts a restaurant that serves a delectable of Asian and international cuisines including buffet and ala cart breakfast, lunch and dinner.

column5: {'label': 'Sovann Phum Hotel, 040802 កំពង់ឆ្នាំង, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពង់ឆ្នាំង', 'city': 'កំពង់ឆ្នាំង', 'district': 'កំពង់ឆ្នាំង', 'postalCode': '040802'}
column19:
Looking for a place to stay in Kampong Chhnang? Then look no further than Sovann Phum Hotel, a budget friendly small hotel that brings the best of Kampong Chhnang to your doorstep.
As your “home away from home,” the small hotel rooms offer air conditioning, and getting online is easy, with free wifi available.
Guests have access to a 24 hour front desk, room service, and a concierge while staying at Sovann Phum Hotel. In addition, Sovann Phum Hotel offers an on-site restaurant, which will help make your Kampong Chhnang trip additionally gratifying. And, as an added convenience, there is free parking available to guests.
For those interested in checking out Ondong Rossey (2.4 mi) while visiting Kampong Chhnang, Sovann Phum Hotel is a short distance away.
If you’re looking for something to do, Cambodia’s Kampong Chhnang floating village (0.0 mi) is a nice way to spend some time, and it is within walking distance of Sovann Phum Hotel.
We’re sure you’ll enjoy your stay at Sovann Phum Hotel as you experience everything Kampong Chhnang has to offer.

column19: Lin Ratanak Angkor Hotel Situated along the enhancing National Road 06 and the closest to local market(Samaki Market), Lin Ratanak Angkor Hotel offers an ideal urban getaway in the heritage land of ancient city. Choose a relaxing home-from-home at Lin Ratanak Angkor Hotel just 15 minutes' drive from Siem Reap International Airport and we provide the free transfer to town 5 minutes' drive to Pub Street and old market area. This affordable Four Star Rating Hotel features 100 room accommodations with complimentary WiFi connection throughout the hotel, ambient dining options, elegant swimming and leisure facilities that satisfy the needs of both business and leisure travelers. The Lin Ratanak Angkor Hotel adds the most preferred services including baby siting, concierge service, on-call medical treatment, and the traditional show set by the pool pavilion that inspire your accommodation an ease. From the minute you step inside the bright, welcoming lobby of Lin Ratanak Angkor Hotel, you will feel at home and experience with the service and hospitality of Cambodians.

column19: Raffles Grand Hotel d'Angkor has been open in the heart of Siem Reap since 1932, and was the first luxury hotel to provide elegant accommodation to travellers eager to discover the marvels of Angkor Wat. The hotel is a 10-minute drive from the Angkor UNESCO World Heritage Site and a 50-minute drive from Siem Reap International Airport. Grand Hotel d'Angkor features an award-winning swimming pool, fitness centre, spa, tennis courts and a one-of-a-kind cultural resort programme. Set in over 15 acres of beautifully landscaped French gardens, the accommodation blends old-world charm with Cambodian influences and contemporary details. Rooms, suites and villas are characterised by beautifully refined interiors, hardwood floors, traditional ceiling fans, brass rotary telephones, high-speed wi-fi, 24-hour Raffles butler service and stunning views of either the iconic swimming pool or the expansive gardens.

column19:
If you’re looking for a budget friendly hotel in Phnom Penh, look no further than Meng Goldiana 282 Hotel.
For those interested in checking out popular landmarks while visiting Phnom Penh, Meng Goldiana 282 Hotel is located a short distance from Bassac Lane (0.4 mi) and Bophana Center (0.5 mi).
Rooms at Meng Goldiana 282 Hotel provide air conditioning, a refrigerator, and a minibar, and guests can stay connected with free wifi.
In addition, while staying at Meng Goldiana 282 Hotel guests have access to room service. You can also enjoy a pool and an on-site restaurant. Need a place to park? Free parking is available at Meng Goldiana 282 Hotel.
While in Phnom Penh, you may want to check out some of the restaurants that are a short walk away from Meng Goldiana 282 Hotel, including Eclipse Sky Bar (0.4 mi), Romdeng (0.7 mi), and Friends the Restaurant (0.9 mi).
Looking to explore? Then look no further than Tuol Sleng Genocide Museum (0.6 mi), Royal Palace (0.8 mi), and Central Market (0.9 mi), which are some popular Phnom Penh attractions – all conveniently located within walking distance of the hotel.
The staff at Meng Goldiana 282 Hotel looks forward to serving you during your upcoming visit.

See why so many travelers make Romdoul Farm Residence their small hotel of choice when visiting Kampong Thom. Providing an ideal mix of value, comfort and convenience, it offers a budget friendly setting with an array of amenities designed for travelers like you.

At Romdoul Farm Residence, your comfort and satisfaction come first, and they look forward to welcoming you to Kampong Thom.

column19: The first 4-star standard hotel, GLORIOUS HOTEL & SPA, welcomes you in to discover the hidden history of the well-known tourist site in Kampong Thom, Sambor Prei Kuk temple. The charm of Kampong Thom is not only a major tourist town, but it is definitely a perfect place to visit and explore the real Cambodia without the crowds as the other cities. There are more than a few temples to see in the area including Angkorian temples such as Sambor Prei Kuk. The complex belongs to the Pre-Angkorian era of Chenla (late 6th to 9th centuries), and it was one of its ancient capitals known then as Ishanapura, which is only 20 kilometres from the town centre. Glorious Hotel & Spa is elegantly designed to be your home away from home as well as the ideal venue for both leisure and business travelers who expect superior hospitality, high class amenities, and friendly services from the experienced, well-trained and multilingual staff who will serve you from the heart.

column19:
See why so many travelers make Sokchea Chantha Guest House their small hotel of choice when visiting Kampong Thom. Providing an ideal mix of value, comfort and convenience, it offers an array of amenities designed for travelers like you.
Guest rooms offer a flat screen TV, air conditioning, and a desk, and Sokchea Chantha Guest House makes getting online easy as free wifi is available.
You can also take advantage of some of the amenities offered by the small hotel, including room service, currency exchange, and baggage storage. As an added convenience, there is free parking available to guests.
Guests of Sokchea Chantha Guest House can find some great restaurants a short walk from the small hotel, including Arunras Hotel (0.7 mi), Love Cafe & Pizza (0.7 mi), and Sambor Village Restaurant and Bar (0.7 mi).
We’re sure you’ll enjoy your stay at Sokchea Chantha Guest House as you experience all of the things Kampong Thom has to offer.

column19:
Welcome to Arunras Hotel, your Kampong Thom “home away from home.” Arunras Hotel aims to make your visit as relaxing and enjoyable as possible, which is why so many guests continue to come back year after year.
Guest rooms offer amenities such as air conditioning, and guests can go online with free wifi offered by the hotel.
The property also boasts an on-site restaurant, to help make your stay more enjoyable.
While you’re here, be sure to check out some of the Asian restaurants, including Sambor Village Restaurant and Bar and Kampong Thom Restaurant, all of which are a short distance from Arunras Hotel.
Arunras Hotel puts the best of Kampong Thom at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.

column19:
Looking for a place to stay in Phnom Penh? Then look no further than Regent Park Hotel, a budget friendly hotel that brings the best of Phnom Penh to your doorstep.
Rooms at Regent Phnom Penh provide air conditioning, and guests can stay connected with free wifi.
In addition, while staying at Phnom Penh Regent guests have access to a 24 hour front desk, 24 hour check-in, and room service. You can also enjoy a lounge. Need a place to park? Parking is available at Regent Phnom Penh.
Given the close proximity of popular landmarks, such as Bassac Lane (0.3 mi) and Champey Academy of Arts (0.7 mi), guests of Phnom Penh Regent can easily experience some of Phnom Penh's most well known attractions.
Phnom Penh has plenty of Italian restaurants. So when you’re here, be sure to check out popular spots like Brooklyn Pizza & Bistro, Piccola Italia Da Luigi, and Oskar Bistro, which are serving up some great dishes.
During your visit, be sure to check out popular attractions like Tuol Sleng Genocide Museum (1.2 mi), Royal Palace (0.5 mi), and Silver Pagoda (0.5 mi), which are all within walking distance of the hotel.
We’re sure you’ll enjoy your stay at Regent Park Hotel as you experience everything Phnom Penh has to offer.

column19:
Finding an ideal small hotel in Kampot does not have to be difficult. Welcome to Om Samol Guesthouse, a nice option for travelers like you.
For those interested in checking out popular landmarks while visiting Kampot, Om Samol Guesthouse is located a short distance from The Old Royal Cinema (1.0 mi) and Farm Link (1.6 mi).
Guest rooms offer a refrigerator and air conditioning.
You can also take advantage of some of the amenities offered by the small hotel, including a 24 hour front desk and baggage storage.
While in Kampot be sure to experience local shawarma favorites at Aroma House.
There is no shortage of things to do in the area: explore popular history museums such as Kampot Museum.
Om Samol Guesthouse looks forward to welcoming you on your visit to Kampot.

column19:
Welcome to Nomad Working Space, your Kampot “home away from home.” Nomad Working Space aims to make your visit as relaxing and enjoyable as possible, which is why so many guests continue to come back year after year.
Given the close proximity of popular landmarks, such as The Old Royal Cinema (0.8 mi) and Farm Link (1.5 mi), guests of Nomad Working Space can easily experience some of Kampot's most well known attractions.
Rooms at Nomad Working Space offer air conditioning providing exceptional comfort and convenience, and guests can go online with free wifi.
A 24 hour front desk, baggage storage, and a sun terrace are some of the conveniences offered at this small hotel. An on-site restaurant will also help to make your stay even more special. If you are driving to Nomad Working Space, free parking is available.
While you’re here, be sure to check out some of the Chinese restaurants, including Ecran Noodle and Dumpling House and Kama, all of which are a short distance from Nomad Working Space.
Should time allow, Kampot Art Gallery is a popular art gallery that is relatively easy to get to.
Nomad Working Space puts the best of Kampot at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.

column19: Nestled within lush green gardens, Kampot Sweet Boutique offers accommodation away from the hustle and bustle of Kampot. The outdoor swimming pool as well aspool bar is accessible. Guests can enjoy a meal at the in-house restaurant. A continental breakfast is available daily at Sweet Restaurant. All units are equipped with private balcony, pool view & pool access, air conditioning, a flat-screen TV with setline, a fridge, a kettle, a shower, a hairdryer and a desk. At the hotel each room includes a wardrobe and a private bathroom. Every effort is made to make guests feel comfortable. To do so, the property provides the best in services and amenities. Top features of the property include free Wi-Fi in all rooms, 24-hour security, daily housekeeping, Just a short ride 1km to Kampot Provincial Museum, while Kampot Night Market is 1.8 km away. The nearest airport is Sihanoukville International, 60 km from the hotel, and the property offers a paid airport shuttle service.

column5: {'label': 'Sabay Beach Kampot, 070801 កំពត, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'កំពត', 'district': 'កំពង់កណ្ដាល', 'postalCode': '070801'}
column19: Sabay Beach: Tranquil riverside retreat in Kampot with scenic sunset views over Bokor National Park. A small selection of nine rooms is available, some riverside, others in an organic mango garden. Choose modern air-con or rustic wooden charm, each with a King Size Bed and private bathroom. Unique French architect-designed treehouses, European-Asian fusion cuisine from a menu entirely created by French chefs in our restaurant, and signature cocktails made with different Kampot peppers. Enjoy fresh dishes and attentive service from our Cambodian Front Of House team. Positioned upstream from town, Sabay Beach invites you to swim in a pollution-free environment. Reception can arrange Tuktuks to town or taxis to Phnom Penh Airport. Escape to Sabay Beach: Unparalleled service, stunning views, and lush surroundings. Book your retreat for nature's embrace with unmatched hospitality. Sabay Beach, Refined by Nature.

column5: {'label': 'Two Moons Hotel, 070801 កំពត, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'កំពត', 'district': 'កំពង់កណ្ដាល', 'postalCode': '070801'}
column19: Set in a tranquil location to a backdrop of river and mountain views makes Two Moons the perfect choice for a relaxing stay yet only minutes to the center of town. The hotel is located on the main riverside street and the heart of Kampot province, yet far enough to benefit of the calm and tranquility of nature. Turn left and walk 200m and you are in a local fishing village with its early morning seafood market; a colorful display of large and small fishing boats on the go in an area primarily populated by Cambodian’s belonging to the ethnic group known as Cham, a reference to an ancient empire of warriors. Turn right and stroll along the beautifully upgraded riverside promenade, passing the newly built governors mansion and in to town just a ten minute walk away. We offer twenty rooms in total with a wide variety of accommodation options including wooden bungalows, a traditional Khmer wooden house and a fourteen up market hotel rooms with views over the river.

column5: {'label': 'Kool Kampot, 070801 កំពត, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'កំពត', 'district': 'កំពង់កណ្ដាល', 'postalCode': '070801'}
column19: Kool Kampot is a British owned and run guesthouse on the riverfront of Prek Tuek Chhou River, providing comfortable, secure, and affordable accommodation with free high-speed WiFi throughout the building. The property is a short stroll along the riverside esplanade to the main bars, restaurants, and shops of Kampot town. Our private superior and standard rooms are all fitted with both air conditioning and ceiling fans. Our private double room with shared bathroom comes with a ceiling fan. All rooms include bed linen, bath towels, complimentary toiletries, hot shower, fridge, closet, private safe, kettle, tea, coffee, and bottled water. Our spacious six-bed dormitory is air conditioned from 7pm to 7am, and a hot high-pressure shower in the bathroom. Each bunk gets its own fan, light, and power outlet. Dorm beds come with two pillows and a blanket, bath towels, complimentary toiletries, a water dispenser, shelves and closet space, plus a large private locker for each guest. Free high-speed WiFi (60mbps) is available in all rooms, private balconies, lounge areas, the terrace, and the rooftop bar. The unique building dating from the 1960s retains visible scars of Cambodia’s troubled history, and provides a large rooftop area where guests can relax and enjoy bar drinks while taking in spectacular views of Bokor Mountain and the river. The rooftop is the ideal place to practice dawn yoga, watch sunsets or electrical storms, or simply star gaze late into the night. The lower terrace offers similar views but offers more privacy and shade from the midday sun, and is the perfect place to relax, catch up on emails, play the guitar or read books in one of several hammocks, or try your skill with some pool or billiards with friends or other guests. Kool Kampot offers two additional indoor quiet lounge areas with sofas, tables, and ceiling fans. Creative travellers, artists, musicians, and writers are particularly fond of the location for its tranquility, atmosphere, and views. Kool Kampot can arrange local tours, onwards travel, scooter hire, and luggage storage. Our foreign and domestic staff have extensive experience traveling Southeast Asia and are always happy to offer advice and suggestions for sightseeing and activities during your vacation in Kampot. The relaxed and peaceful atmosphere combined with our friendly and helpful staff makes Kool Kampot the ideal place to stay while exploring the town and local tourist attractions.

column5: {'label': "Chey Mean Leap's Villa, 070203 ទឹកឈូរ, កម្ពុជា", 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'ទឹកឈូរ', 'district': 'កំពង់ក្រែង', 'postalCode': '070203'}
column19:
Chey Mean Leap's Villa is an excellent choice for travelers visiting Kampot, offering many helpful amenities designed to enhance your stay.
You’ll enjoy relaxing rooms that offer a refrigerator, a kitchenette, and air conditioning, and you can stay connected during your stay as Chey Mean Leap's Villa offers guests free wifi.
The small hotel features room service, a sun terrace, and express check-in and check-out. Plus, Chey Mean Leap's Villa offers a pool and free breakfast, providing a pleasant respite from your busy day. For guests with a vehicle, free parking is available.
When you’re feeling hungry, be sure to check out Gringo Loco and El Taco Bar, which are some Mexican restaurants that are popular with locals and out-of-towners alike.
Looking to explore? Then look no further than Farm Link (1.1 mi), which is a popular Kampot attraction – and it is conveniently located within walking distance of the small hotel.
Enjoy your stay in Kampot!

column19: Designer Vireak Chandara discovered the paradise "Mlech Dam" in 2018 – a breathtaking spot with a ring of mountains and a lake. Inspired, he created The Safari, an exclusive campsite with unique lotus tents (launched in 2019). The love for nature resonated with guests, and Dara envisioned an evolution. He craved to offer on-site accommodations while maintaining a natural connection. The answer? Diamond-shaped cabins, mirror the tents but with added comfort. Over two years, Dara and his wife transformed the site. Challenges were met, and ten magnificent diamond cabins rose. The Safari boasts a one-of-a-kind design, with meticulous attention to detail both inside and out. As a dedicated artist, Dara is constantly refining the décor and crafting exciting outdoor activities. The Safari is an ongoing masterpiece, a testament to Dara's vision. Experience tranquility embraced by the brilliance of a diamond. The Safari is just 100km away from Phnom Penh via NR3 and NR45.

column19:
Welcome to Popok Vel Guesthouse, your Kampot “home away from home.” Popok Vel Guesthouse aims to make your visit as relaxing and enjoyable as possible, which is why so many guests continue to come back year after year.
Given the close proximity to The Old Royal Cinema (0.5 mi), guests of Popok Vel Guesthouse can easily experience one of Kampot's most popular landmarks.
Rooms at Popok Vel Guesthouse offer air conditioning and a seating area providing exceptional comfort and convenience, and guests can go online with free wifi.
A 24 hour front desk, room service, and currency exchange are some of the conveniences offered at this small hotel. If you are driving to Popok Vel Guesthouse, parking is available.
If you’re looking for a barbeque restaurant, consider a visit to Rusty Keyhole or The Sunflower, which are all conveniently located a short distance from Popok Vel Guesthouse.
If you’re looking for something to do, Farm Link (0.6 mi) is a nice way to spend some time, and it is within walking distance of Popok Vel Guesthouse.
Popok Vel Guesthouse puts the best of Kampot at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.

column19:

column19: Om Sweet Home is a homestay run by an Italian family that welcomes you with great breakfasts and tasty Italian, Indian and Khmer homemade dishes. You can rent a scooter and enjoy the experience to explore Kampot and its beautiful countryside where you can see the best local spots: caves, nature, culture, food, hidden lakes where you can swim, pepper plantations and more! Om Sweet Home even offers amazing tours with specialized guides throughout Cambodia by booking directly the local buses with on-site pick-up with the possibility to move anywhere in Cambodia, Vietnam, Laos and Thailand. All this and more in Om Sweet Home where all the world is welcome!

column19: Located in Kampot, 2.4 km from Kampot Pagoda, Sunny Hotel Kampot features a garden and views of the city. This 3-star hotel offers a tour desk. The property provides a 24-hour front desk, a shared lounge and currency exchange for guests. At the hotel each room comes with air conditioning, a desk, a balcony with a river view, a private bathroom, a flat-screen TV, bed linen and towels. Sunny Hotel Kampot has certain rooms with mountain views, and all rooms are equipped with an electric tea pot. Guest rooms include a safety deposit box. Kampot Night Market is a 2-minute walk from the accommodation, while Kampot Provincial Museum is 1.1 km away. The nearest airport is Sihanoukville International Airport, 59.5 km from Sunny Hotel Kampot.

column5: {'label': 'Nakru Guesthouse and Restaurant, 070803 កំពត, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'កំពត', 'district': 'កំពង់បាយ', 'postalCode': '070803'}
column19:
Everyone needs a place to lay their weary head. For travelers visiting Kampot, Nakru Guesthouse and Restaurant is an excellent choice for rest and rejuvenation. Well-known for its budget friendly environment and proximity to great restaurants and attractions, Nakru Guesthouse and Restaurant makes it easy to enjoy the best of Kampot.
You’ll enjoy relaxing rooms that offer air conditioning, and you can stay connected during your stay as Nakru Guesthouse and Restaurant offers guests free wifi.
The guest house features currency exchange, shops, and newspaper. Plus, Nakru Guesthouse and Restaurant offers an on-site restaurant, providing a pleasant respite from your busy day. For guests with a vehicle, free parking is available.
The Old Royal Cinema (0.2 mi), located nearby, makes Nakru Guesthouse and Restaurant a great place to stay for those interested in visiting this popular Kampot landmark.
When you’re feeling hungry, be sure to check out Le Comptoir de Kampot, which is a wine bar that is popular with locals and out-of-towners alike.
Looking for something to do in Kampot? Farm Link (0.6 mi) is a popular attraction that is within walking distance of Nakru Guesthouse and Restaurant.
Nakru Guesthouse and Restaurant is sure to make your visit to Kampot one worth remembering.

column5: {'label': "Samon's Village, 070804 កំពត, កម្ពុជា", 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'កំពត', 'district': 'អណ្ដូងខ្មែរ', 'postalCode': '070804'}
column19: Here at Samon's Village we strive to give you a truly authentic Khmer experience. Our aim is first and foremost to promote and share Khmer culture. Our relaxing atmosphere will help you find the space to unwind and really feel the pulse of Khmer life. Our village has been built and designed to recreate the feeling of a Khmer village from the past. Each of our bungalows is unique and built entirely from locally sourced materials using traditional techniques. Our kitchen uses only local sourced produce and organic free-range meats to prepare delicious typical Khmer home food. We have regular music and dance events to share our artistic traditions with you. You will have the opportunity to experience our tours or activities and have an authentic insight of Khmer daily life. In doing this we hope to reinforce our cultural identity while giving you an opportunity to experience Khmer life first hand. You won't find a better place to experience the joyous and peaceful philosophy of the small towns and villages that define this country.
