column19:
See why so many travelers make Kampongbay Makeng Guesthouse their small hotel of choice when visiting Kampot. Providing an ideal mix of value, comfort and convenience, it offers an array of amenities designed for travelers like you.
As your “home away from home,” the small hotel rooms offer air conditioning, and getting online is easy, with free wifi available.
Guests have access to a 24 hour front desk while staying at Kampongbay Makeng Guesthouse. In addition, Kampongbay Makeng Guesthouse offers an on-site restaurant, which will help make your Kampot trip additionally gratifying. And, as an added convenience, there is free parking available to guests.
Close to The Old Royal Cinema (0.5 mi), a popular Kampot landmark, Kampongbay Makeng Guesthouse is a great destination for tourists.
While in Kampot, you may want to check out some of the restaurants that are a short walk away from Kampongbay Makeng Guesthouse, including Rusty Keyhole (0.5 mi), Epic Arts Cafe (0.5 mi), and bARACA restaurant (0.5 mi).
If you’re looking for things to do, you can check out Farm Link (0.3 mi), which is a popular attraction amongst tourists, and it is within walking distance.
We’re sure you’ll enjoy your stay at Kampongbay Makeng Guesthouse as you experience all of the things Kampot has to offer.

column5: {'label': 'Ganesha Kampot, 070203 ទឹកឈូរ, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'ទឹកឈូរ', 'district': 'កំពង់ក្រែង', 'postalCode': '070203'}
column19: Ganesha Kampot has been designed with your spatial experience in mind.. We are an unusually low density guesthouse, of just 9 private units and 4 rooms, spread across 4 hectare, amid rich mangrove and tropical gardens. We welcome you to create unique memories in our hidden paradise, away from the high density and hustle of Asian cities.. Off of the beaten track, your experience starts upon an adventurous transit to Ganesha Kampot, taking a ride through breathtaking scenery, rice paddies and the beautiful surrounding mountains. We are located in Kampot Province, we are on the outskirts of Kampot city center, close enough to cycle, grab a tuk tuk or take the 10 minute drive. We welcome people who seek to immerse themselves in the culture and feel of an authentic Cambodia. Ganesha Kampot offers the perfect serene location for yoga, meditation, photography, reading or the simple luxury of granting yourself time and space, for you! Gaze at the crystal clear Milky Way on the balcony of your very own Tribal Hut in the garden, or enjoy the stunning 360 panoramic views from the top of The Tower. Wander in the incredible tropical garden, take a lazy boat ride down the river drift along in our traditional Khmer canoe or explore the beautiful Kampot countryside on one of our mountain bikes. During your stay here we are happy to introduce you to the extensive choice of outdoor activities, as well as directing you to our favourite local businesses in Kampot. Our restaurant offers both local Khmer cuisine, and Western dishes, all lovingly and expertly prepared by our amazing kitchen staff. We have a large menu for vegans and vegetarians and our staff would be happy to cater for your dietary requirements. Our bar also offers a wide selection of natural fruit drinks as well as cocktails, wines and spirits. Your inimitable stay in the heart of the Kingdom of Cambodia awaits at Ganesha Kampot... See you soon! The Ganesha Family

column19: A true Eco Resort, Eden offers riverside accommodation in an ethnic Cham village 5 km from kampot town. Natural bungalows feature large doors which open to a view of river and mountains and a swimming deck built over the river itself. Guests can enjoy incredible organic Khmer cuisine and locally inspired cocktails on their own private deck or in our relaxing common areas. All bungalows use bright solar lighting and have en-suite eco toilets. There is plenty to discover in the village and maps are available for detailed self guided bicycle tours. Free Kayaks, Morning Yoga classes, bicycles, swim tubes, and fishing tackle!

column19: Om Sweet Home is a homestay run by an Italian family that welcomes you with great breakfasts and tasty Italian, Indian and Khmer homemade dishes. You can rent a scooter and enjoy the experience to explore Kampot and its beautiful countryside where you can see the best local spots: caves, nature, culture, food, hidden lakes where you can swim, pepper plantations and more! Om Sweet Home even offers amazing tours with specialized guides throughout Cambodia by booking directly the local buses with on-site pick-up with the possibility to move anywhere in Cambodia, Vietnam, Laos and Thailand. All this and more in Om Sweet Home where all the world is welcome!

column19: Kampot Cabana features rustic wooden bungalows built over the river, amidst calming greenery. Free WiFi is available in public areas. Located in Cambodia’s Andung Khmer Village, Kampot Cabana is 1.5 km from the city centre. The guesthouse provides motorbike rentals. Tuk-Tuk tours and bus tickets can be arranged at the reception desk. Each bungalow is fan-cooled, and comes with a mosquito net. Bathroom and toilet facilities are shared. Laundry facilities are available. Kampot Cabana serves food and drinks at the bar from 07:30 to 21:00. Guests can also enjoy views of the sunset from the terrace.

column19: 'Every person counts!' Epic Arts Café is a thriving social enterprise, with 100% of the profits funding our charity. We believe that, together, we can build a society where every person counts. Founded in 2006, our Café is an inclusive workplace, serving a amazing breakfast and a flavour-packed lunch. In our Creations Shop upstairs you'll find artisanal souvenirs and gifts with a purpose, handmade by our students. Your support will help our disabled students not only learn the arts but become part of a supportive community that believes they can achieve, whatever their ability. Thank you for choosing to support Epic Arts!

column5: {'label': 'Little Garden Restaurant and Guesthouse, 070803 កំពត, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'កំពត', 'district': 'កំពង់បាយ', 'postalCode': '070803'}
column19:
Finding an ideal small hotel in Kampot does not have to be difficult. Welcome to Little Garden Guesthouse & Restaurant, a nice option for travelers like you.
Guest rooms offer air conditioning, and Little Garden Guesthouse & Restaurant makes getting online easy as free wifi is available.
You can also take advantage of some of the amenities offered by the small hotel, including room service. In addition, guests can enjoy an on-site restaurant during their visit. As an added convenience, there is free parking available to guests.
The Old Royal Cinema (0.2 mi), located nearby, makes Little Garden Guesthouse & Restaurant a great place to stay for those interested in visiting this popular Kampot landmark.
While you’re here, be sure to check out some of the sushi restaurants, including Flowers Nanobrewery and Rainbow Bridge Japanese Restaurant, all of which are a short distance from Little Garden Guesthouse & Restaurant.
There is no shortage of things to do in the area: explore popular art galleries such as Kampot Art Gallery.
Little Garden Guesthouse & Restaurant puts the best of Kampot at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.

column19: Mekong River CruiseCai - Rang Floating Market Tours - Touring a floating market in the Mekong Delta is a box that many travellers to Saigon wish to check, and none are bigger, or more popular than the Can Tho’s Cai Rang Floating Market.The Cai Rang Floating Market, the largest wholesale floating market in the Mekong Delta, starts around 04:00 and runs until 10:00, meaning that you’ll have to get an early start of the day if you want to visit.The market is about six kilometres from Can Tho, or about a 40-minute boat ride. While floating down the river, you get a glimpse of life along its shores. You’ll pass vibrantly painted boats anchored along the shore, merchant vessels carrying loads down the river and houses built on stilts over the water.Once you finally reach the market, it’s an impressive site. A stretch of boats selling all variety of goods lines the river.

column19:
If you’re looking for a quaint guest house in Kampot, look no further than Man'Groove Guesthouse.
Guest rooms offer amenities such as air conditioning, a desk, and a mosquito net, and guests can go online with free wifi offered by the guest house.
Man'Groove Guesthouse features room service and outdoor furniture, to help make your stay more enjoyable. The property also boasts an on-site restaurant. If you are driving to Man'Groove Guesthouse, free parking is available.
Should time allow, The Old Royal Cinema is a popular historic site that is relatively easy to get to.
The staff at Man'Groove Guesthouse looks forward to serving you during your upcoming visit.

column19: We are in love with our Kampong, but nonetheless we will now write here all the negatives, because since we decided to open to the public I've been reading reviews of guesthouses of Kampot in Tripadvisor and I've been growing scared of disappointing people that come here with too high expectations. If you are looking for a resort with luxuries this is not the place. We tried our best to make our bungalows comfortable and we struggle to keep them clean. But yes, you will have to put up with mosquitoes, bugs, lizards, birds. We clean the beach everyday and sometimes several times a day but depending on the ties and the season the beach can be dirty and the water unappealing. There is no rubbish collection in the village and this means we have to burn the rubbish we pick up from the beach and we produce. It can be a smelly and smokey job! column19: Nestled within lush green gardens, Kampot Sweet Boutique offers accommodation away from the hustle and bustle of Kampot. The outdoor swimming pool as well aspool bar is accessible. Guests can enjoy a meal at the in-house restaurant. A continental breakfast is available daily at Sweet Restaurant. All units are equipped with private balcony, pool view & pool access, air conditioning, a flat-screen TV with setline, a fridge, a kettle, a shower, a hairdryer and a desk. column19:
Looking for a place to stay in Kampot? Then look no further than Bokor Sun Set Guesthouse, a guest house that brings the best of Kampot to your doorstep.
Free wifi is offered to guests, and rooms at Bokor Sun Set Guesthouse offer air conditioning.
During your stay, take advantage of some of the amenities offered, including baggage storage. For travelers arriving by car, free parking is available.
While staying at Bokor Sun Set Guesthouse, visitors can check out The Old Royal Cinema (0.8 mi), which is a popular Kampot attraction.
While in Kampot, you may want to check out some of the restaurants that are a short walk away from Bokor Sun Set Guesthouse, including Rusty Keyhole (0.8 mi), Epic Arts Cafe (0.9 mi), and bARACA restaurant (0.9 mi).
Best of all, Bokor Sun Set Guesthouse makes it easy to experience some great Kampot attractions like Kampot Art Gallery, which is a popular art gallery.
We’re sure you’ll enjoy your stay at Bokor Sun Set Guesthouse as you experience everything Kampot has to offer.

column19:
Family-run guesthouse with four comfortable superior double rooms in a quiet and safe location in Kampot, Kingdom of Cambodia. Only 4 minutes by TukTuk from the city centre. A warm welcome!

Our superior rooms feature a king-size bed, guaranteeing you a restful night's sleep. The room is equipped with a minibar (extra charge). The air conditioning ensures a pleasant room temperature even on hot days. Numerous other extras, such as a welcome cocktail and two bottles of water free of charge on arrival, as well as a family atmosphere will make your stay pleasant. You have your own bathroom with shower and hot water.

column19: Your home away from home. Karma Traders is located in a quiet area about 1.5kms from the center of town. We offer a refreshing swimming pool with bar, family dinners, rooftop bar/restaurant with views of Bokor National Park, cinema room, ping pong table, and 5x free WiFi networks throughout the property. Our rooftop cocktail bar has stunning sunrise and sunset views, with breakfast, lunch and dinner served daily. Happy hour 5-7pm everyday, enjoy 25% off all alcohol. Don't miss our live music nights every Tuesday and pub quiz every Sunday evenings. We can organise all ongoing travel, scooter rental, local recommendations and can offer advice on planning your journey. Whatever you need, our friendly fleet of staff are here to help!

column19: Bohemiaz resort & spa is the perfect place to relax and rejuvenate. Located only 4km from town it’s the perfect mix of being immersed in the stunning countryside whilst also being close enough to pop in. There is a range of beautiful air-con & fan rooms as well as small 4 person dorms to suit every budget. We have a fantastic new spa complex complete with gym, Jacuzzi, infrared sauna, herbal steam room & private treatment rooms. Entry to the spa is free for all guests staying at Bohemiaz. Our restaurant serves up a mix of western & Khmer food, some healthy like our superfood granola, create your own salad or vegan curries, some naughty like our giant burger or homemade cakes! Our healthy food and drinks have been developed with a nutritionist, we know that making small changes can make a big difference on your health and well being, we have vegetarian, vegan and gluten free options and make our own nut milk. Discounted yoga classes available daily at yoga barn kampot only 200m walk!

Borey Bokor is an excellent choice for travelers visiting Kampot, offering a budget friendly environment alongside many helpful amenities designed to enhance your stay.
You’ll enjoy relaxing rooms that offer air conditioning, and you can stay connected during your stay as Borey Bokor offers guests free internet access.
For guests with a vehicle, free parking is available.
The Old Royal Cinema (0.1 mi), located nearby, makes Borey Bokor a great place to stay for those interested in visiting this popular Kampot landmark.
While you’re here, be sure to check out some of the Chinese restaurants, including Ecran Noodle and Dumpling House and Kama, all of which are a short distance from Borey Bokor.
Looking to explore? Then look no further than Farm Link (0.6 mi), which is a popular Kampot attraction – and it is conveniently located within walking distance of the hotel.
Enjoy your stay in Kampot!

column19:
Welcome to Borey Chulsa Guesthouse, your Kampot “home away from home.” Borey Chulsa Guesthouse aims to make your visit as relaxing and enjoyable as possible, which is why so many guests continue to come back year after year.
Close to The Old Royal Cinema (0.7 mi), a popular Kampot landmark, Borey Chulsa Guesthouse is a great destination for tourists.
Free wifi is offered to guests, and rooms at Borey Chulsa Guesthouse offer air conditioning and a desk.
During your stay, take advantage of some of the amenities offered, including a concierge.
If you like Asian restaurants, Borey Chulsa Guesthouse is conveniently located near Epic Arts Cafe, Ecran Noodle and Dumpling House, and Rikitikitavi.
If you are interested in exploring Kampot, check out a waterfall, such as Popokvil Waterfall.
Borey Chulsa Guesthouse puts the best of Kampot at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.

column5: {'label': 'Champey Bokor Guesthouse, 070804 កំពត, កម្ពុជា', 'countryCode': 'KHM', 'countryName': 'កម្ពុជា', 'county': 'កំពត', 'city': 'កំពត', 'district': 'អណ្ដូងខ្មែរ', 'postalCode': '070804'}
column19:
See why so many travelers make Champey Bokor Guesthouse their small hotel of choice when visiting Kampot. Providing an ideal mix of value, comfort and convenience, it offers an array of amenities designed for travelers like you.
Guest rooms offer air conditioning, and Champey Bokor Guesthouse makes getting online easy as free wifi is available.
You can also take advantage of some of the amenities offered by the small hotel, including a 24 hour front desk and baggage storage.
For those interested in checking out The Old Royal Cinema (0.8 mi) while visiting Kampot, Champey Bokor Guesthouse is a short distance away.
Kampot has plenty of cafes. So when you’re here, be sure to check out popular spots like Epic Arts Cafe, Simple Things, and Cafe Espresso Kampot, which are serving up some great dishes.
Kampot is also home to Kampot Museum, a popular history museum that is not too far from Champey Bokor Guesthouse.
We’re sure you’ll enjoy your stay at Champey Bokor Guesthouse as you experience all of the things Kampot has to offer.

column19: Not just another bike tour, we aim to provide a complete historical and cultural experience while cycling the scenic Kampot countryside. From the rise of the Khmer Empire to the fall of the Khmer Rouge, our guide will take you through the history of Cambodia as we take frequent breaks. We will tour several different temples while giving explanation of how Buddhism, Animism and Hinduism blend to form the Cambodian world-view, and explain some of Cambodia's fascinating legends and myths. Our tour includes lunch at a local family's home where you can sample some authentic home-cooked Cambodian cuisine. The perfect tour if you've want to know more about the fascinating country of Cambodia.

column19:
Hello, my name is Sophia from Lucky Kitchen Cooking Class & Sophia’s Kitchen Kampot.
To begin our cooking class, we meet each other at 10:00AM near the market. We visit the market, make shopping together and after we take one TukTuk to my rooftop.
We start cooking class and begin to prepare the food. For one cooking class session, the group can choose 3 meals and 1 dessert.

You decide if you want with meat or only vegetarian food, also you can ask for a specific plate of your choice…
Fresh lime juice and tea are free of course.

Price is 22$/person.
One option: cook with seafood cost 27$ per person.
Please choose the meals you want to cook, thanks you and please contact me by WhatsApp or Telegram if possible.
My phone number is +85510261391
Sophia NOV
